    <string name="privileged_mode_description">Configure granular security relaxation for nested virtualization or advanced hardware access.</string>
    <string name="privileged_nomask_desc">Disable jail masks to allow write access to /proc and /sys. Note: /sys remains read-only unless Hardware Access is also enabled.</string>
    <string name="privileged_nocaps_desc">Do not drop any Linux capabilities (full root power).</string>
    <string name="privileged_noseccomp_desc">Disable Seccomp syscall filtering. This enables advanced kernel features like unprivileged user namespaces, strictly required for nested sandboxing (Bubblewrap, Flatpak) and also allows loading out-of-tree kernel modules.</string>
    <string name="privileged_shared_desc">Enable MS_SHARED mount propagation to the host.</string>
    <string name="privileged_unfiltered_desc">Bypass device filtering. All host /dev nodes become visible.</string>
    <string name="privileged_full_desc">Enable all privileged flags at once.</string>
